Kobalt is a 2d game engine written in Java. It currently
has the following features:
	
	- Loading and managing 2d sprites
	- Collission detection using arbitrary shapes
	- A particle effects engine
	- A library of raster graphics effects
	- Loading and playing WAV and MIDI files in the background

==================
Build Instructions
==================
Kobalt was built using Eclipse. To be able to build this project
and run the demos, simply import this directory as a project in
Eclipse. The demos are in a package called tester.

Note: The Makefile is still incomplete. Use it to clean up
.class files before committing the code.
